{"name": "typemedaddy", "metadata": {"name": "typemedaddy", "version": "0.5", "classifiers": [], "home_page": null, "license": null, "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["autopep8"], "summary": "Derives type hints from data captured during runtime. Updates source files with type hints. USE SOURCE CONTROL before running!!!!", "upload_time": 1733244173}, "documentation": ["# CAUTION!!!\nThis lib will OVERWRITE YOUR SOURCE FILES! ( It creates backup files before it does )\nUse SOURCE CONTROL before running this !!!!\n\nThis is a hobby project, not a production ready stuff.\nI'm not a 'good' programmer - no classes or clean code over here, just procedural spaghetti.\n\n# WHAT?\nThis lib can inspect the data passed to your functions, figure out types from that data and update your function signatures with type info.\n\n# WHY?\nI maintain a legacy project that has no typing at all. \nIt's thousands of lines of code and I have no idea what goes in or out.\nThis is my feeble attemt to remedy this problem automagically.\n\n# REQUIREMENTS\nAt minimum 3.5 - I haven't tested properly.\nIdeally use 3.9 or higher ( This lib supports both Union and '|' )\n\n# INSTALL\n```bash\npip install typemedaddy\n```\n\n# HOW?\n```python\nfrom typemedaddy.typemedaddy import trace, type_it_like_its_hot\n\nwith trace() as trace_data:\n    your_script()\ntype_it_like_its_hot(trace_data)\n```\n\n# Notes to myself\n## Build\n`python setup.py bdist_wheel && rm -rf build && rm -rf *egg-info`\n## Publish\n`twine dist/*`\ntoken is defined in `$HOME/.pypirc`\n"], "modules": [{"name": "typemedaddy.typemedaddy", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "typemedaddy.typemedaddy.is_class", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "obj", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "typemedaddy.typemedaddy.trace", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": ["we use context for easy testing, same with the RESULT yields, for tests only"]}, {"name": "typemedaddy.typemedaddy.is_class_method", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "func_name", "type": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "frame", "type": {"name": "FrameType", "xref": {"fqname": "types.FrameType", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "bool", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.bool", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "typemedaddy.typemedaddy.trace_function", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "frame", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "event", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "arg", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "typemedaddy.typemedaddy.sort_types_none_at_the_end", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "set_of_types", "type": {"name": "Union", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Union", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "set", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.set", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, {"name": "list", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.list", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}]}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "list", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.list", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "typemedaddy.typemedaddy.get_value_type", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "val", "type": {"name": "Any", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Any", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "str", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.str", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "typemedaddy.typemedaddy.union_types", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "types", "type": {"name": "list", "xref": {"fqname": "functions